  "commentary": "With SPX at 6766.58 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6765 (-18.4B) and positive gamma at 6780 (+10.6B), dealers are in active hedging mode - buying the dip toward 6765 and will aggressively sell any push toward 6780. The BREAKOUT regime with -16.7B total GEX means dealers are amplifying moves in both directions, creating a high-tension zone where any directional break will be violent. Watch 6765 as the key support where dealer buying kicks in hardest, and 6780 as the ceiling where they'll dump gamma.\n\nBottom line: expect wild swings in this tight 15-point range until one side breaks decisively.",
